---
comment: |-
  tsc is the TypeScript compiler. It can be abused to read arbitrary files via error messages and to write controlled output files using the --outFile option.
functions:
  file-read:
  - code: |-
      tsc secret.txt
    contexts:
      unprivileged:
        comment: |-
          Attempts to compile arbitrary files and leaks information through error messages, exposing file existence and sometimes content.
  file-write:
  - code: |-
      tsc valid.ts --outFile filetest.js
    contexts:
      unprivileged:
        comment: |-
          Compiles a TypeScript file and writes output to an arbitrary file, enabling controlled file creation or overwrite.
...
